value.0: I suppose the one needing help is not me, but a dear friend. As you may already know, some of the druids have set out in order to find out what's wrong with the Spirit of the Woods.

One of those druids is Orlane, a childhood friend of mine. They have not returned for quite a while. I fear very much for his safety, so I was wondering if you could go and seek her out. He's a halfling, so perhaps he is hiding in some crevice, away from danger.
I know that you have many tasks before you, but please keep an eye out for him.
Thank you! I shall await here for any news.
Oh no... what has happened to my dear friend?

I... thank you for the news. I can only hope he went quickly and peacefully, but as a druid I know that these spiders like to toy with their victims. I don't have much to offer you, but I hope this small sum of gold can be of benefit to you. Take care, <FirstName>.
I was wondering if you needed help with something.
I have some bad news about your friend Orlane.
I found him in a cavern full of monstrous spiders. He was already dead when I saw him.
